1.definition: a nation, state, or other political unit

sub_terms.a: one founded on law and united by compact or tacit agreement by the people for the common good
sub_terms.b: one in which supreme authority is vested in the people

2.definition: a state of the U.S. used officially of Kentucky, Massachusetts, Pennsylvania, and Virginia

3.definition: an association of self-governing autonomous states more or less loosely associated in a common allegiance (as to the British crown)

4.definition: a political unit having local autonomy but voluntarily united with the U.S. used officially of Puerto Rico and the Northern Mariana Islands
